Definition.WordDefinition: blast off \blast" off\ v. i. to begin ascending from the ground under rocket power; -- of a rocket. [PJC]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
blastoff \blast"off`\ n. the launching of a rocket, especially of a spacecraft, under its own power.
Syn: rocket firing, rocket launching, shoot. [WordNet 1.5]
blast off v : launch with great force; "the rockets were blasted off"
blastoff n : the launching of a missile or spacecraft to a specified destination [syn: {shot}]
